\title{Deployments}

The Concourse team maintains a few deployments. The day will eventually come
when you have to do something to one of them. This page is here for you to
remember when you're panicking.

\section{
  \title{Docs\aux{ (\code{concourse-ci.org})}}{docs-website}

  The \link{Concourse Docs}{https://concourse-ci.org} is the face of Concourse,
  providing the landing page and all documentation for the latest version of
  Concourse.

  The docs are automatically built from the \link{\code{concourse/docs}
  repo}{https://github.com/concourse/docs} and deployed via GitHub pages
  whenever a new version of Concourse is released.
}

\section{
  \title{CI\aux{ (\code{ci.concourse-ci.org})}}{ci-environment}

  \link{CI}{https://ci.concourse-ci.org} is our Concourse instance that
  builds, tests, and ships Concourse itself. It is publicly viewable and also
  hosts a handful of example pipelines which are referenced from the
  documentation \link{here}{https://concourse-ci.org/examples.html}.

